net.bytebuddy.implementation.attribute

Class MethodAttributeAppender.ForMethod

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.bytebuddy.implementation.attribute.MethodAttributeAppender.ForMethod
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MethodAttributeAppender, MethodAttributeAppender.Factory
    Enclosing interface:
    MethodAttributeAppender

    public static class MethodAttributeAppender.ForMethod
extends Object
implements MethodAttributeAppender, MethodAttributeAppender.Factory
    Implementation of a method attribute appender that writes all annotations of a given loaded method to the method that is being created. This includes method and parameter annotations. In order to being able to do so, the target method and the given method must have compatible signatures, i.e. an identical number of method parameters. Otherwise, an exception is thrown when this attribute appender is applied on a method.
